### Explanation
- `cur_max`: max product to current position (not max product before this position)
	- for [1,9,0,2], `cur_max` at index 3 is `2` not `9`, because max product to current position is only 2
- `cur_min`: min product to current position (not min product before this position)
	- for [-1,9,0,2], `cur_min` at index 3 is `2` not `-9`, because min product to current position is only 2; 0 seperated the global min and current min 
- `ans` to get current max product
- case are handled differently depends on whether current number is positive or negative
- if `ans` is 0, nums is something like [-2, 0, -3] or [-2], so we return the max of `nums`
