```
/**
The question seems pretty straigtforward, apart from the fact that we have to take into account negative elements.
Product of subarray can only be positive if the number of negative elements are even.

So we will keep two variables, posMax and negMax
posMax will keep track of the highest positive running product found till now.
negMax will keep track of the lowest negative running product found till now.

There are 3 cases.
If element encountered is positive, we can simply multiply it with posMax to get maximum running product.
negMax will also be updated since the running negative product shall also decrease in value by multiplying it with a positive number

If element encountered is negative, we can multiply it with negMax( lowest negative running product ) to get a positive value . If this is greater than positive running product (posMax) then update it.
We will also update negMax by multiplying nums[i] (negative) with posMax, since it will yield a negative value which might be lesser than our already found running negative product.

If the element is 0, then both running products shall be set to 0 (Note that we only have to consider contiguous subarrays).

An example will make it much more clearer.
Dry run it yourself to understand the algorithm fully
nums[i] - -2         5          -1          -4         2          3
posMax  -2           5          10          20        40         120
negMax  -2          -10         -5         -40       -80        -120
result   0           5          10          20        40         120
**/

class Solution {
public:
    int maxProduct(vector<int>& nums) {
        if(nums.size() == 0){ return 0; }
        if(nums.size() == 1){ return nums[0]; }
        int posMax = 1;
        int negMax = 1;
        int result = 0;        
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            int nextPosMax = 1;
            int nextNegMax = 1;
           if(nums[i] > 0){
               nextPosMax = max(posMax * nums[i], nums[i]);
               nextNegMax = min(negMax * nums[i], nums[i]);
           } else if( nums[i] < 0 ){
               nextPosMax = max(negMax * nums[i], nums[i]);
               nextNegMax = min(posMax * nums[i], nums[i]);
           } else {
              nextPosMax = 0;
              nextNegMax = 0;
           }
            result = max(result, max(nextPosMax, nextNegMax));
            posMax = nextPosMax;
            negMax = nextNegMax;
        }
        return result;
    }
};
