**Algorithm**
* **Approach 1 (Recursion - TLE)**
* call the recursive `dfs` function with each of the `index`
* In the recursive `dfs` function, the base case is to check if the passed `index` is going over the length of the `nums` array
* If not recurse with multiplying the result with the `index` element and increment the `index` for the next recursive call

```
class Solution {
     int max = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
     protected void dfs(int[] nums, int res, int index){
         if (index > nums.length-1)
             return;
         res = res * nums[index];
         max  = Math.max(max, res);
         dfs(nums, res, index+1);    
     }
     public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {
         if (nums.length == 0)
             return 0;

         for (int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
             int res = 1;
             dfs(nums,res, i);
         }
         return max;
     }
```
* **Approach 2 (DP / Kadane's Algorithm Accepted)**
* At each index we make sure to compute three values - overall max, max seen so far, min seen so far
* **maxEndingHere** will store all the max product seen so far 
	* this will be coming from either the current element `nums[i]`
	* or the product of current element with `maxEndingHere` so far
	* or the product of current element with `minEndingHere` so far (two negative can be positive and may be higher)
* **minEndingHere** to store the mininmum product seen so far
	* this will be coming from either the current element itself `nums[i]`
	* or the product of current element with `minEndingHere` so far
	* or the product of current element with `maxEndingHere` (since max Ending here will be updated prior to this, we take the value of `maxEndingHere` just before updating in a temp variable)
* **maxOverall** to store the maximum product that was ever computed while iterating the elements, get the max from `maxOverall` and `maxEndingHere`

```
class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {
        int maxOverall = nums[0];
        int maxEndingHere = nums[0];
        int minEndingHere = nums[0];

        for (int i=1;i<nums.length; i++){
            int tmp = maxEndingHere;
            maxEndingHere = Math.max(nums[i], Math.max(nums[i] * maxEndingHere,nums[i] * minEndingHere));
            minEndingHere = Math.min(nums[i], Math.min(nums[i] * tmp,nums[i] * minEndingHere));
            maxOverall = Math.max(maxOverall, maxEndingHere);
        }
        return maxOverall;
    }
}
```

